author: Christina Rexrode
title: U.S. Bank Profit Fueled By Higher Interest Rates, Lower Taxes
text:
U.S. Bancorp on Wednesday reported better-than-expected quarterly earnings, helped by higher interest rates and lower tax rates.
The Minneapolis-based bank, which is the largest regional bank and the seventh-largest bank in the U.S. by assets, said profit rose 13% to $1.68 billion. Per-share earnings were 96 cents, beating the 94 cents expected by analysts polled by Thomson Reuters.
